listings.title: Xtool D1 Rotary Jig v2 - STL File for 3D Printing Your Own
listings.description:
This is an STL file you can use to print your own Xtool D1 Rotary Jig v2 if you don't want to buy the already printed one located here, 

https://www.etsy.com/listing/1228380064/xtool-d1-ra2-pro-rotary-tool-leveling?click_key=20cfd953c348e3953a149d81d843f5378c6c8a79%3A1228380064&click_sum=836a248c&ga_order=most_relevant&ga_search_type=all&ga_view_type=gallery&ga_search_query=xtool+rotary+jig&ref=search_grid-537162-1-1.

Update: The file you will receive is the next generation which is simpler to print and assemble.

The parts you will need are
- Two (1) M6 10mm nut
- One (1) M6 bolt. The longer the bolt, the more angle you will get on your rotary., you can get
- One (1) flat 22mm x 15mm x 2mm flat magnets from Hobby Lobby. (If you want to take advantage of the magnet base)

To assemble all you need to do is carefully super glue the nut and bolt in their respective spots and snap the ball cover to the base.

It is for your use only, please do not sell the file or printed product to others.

listings.title: Wyze Camera mount v2 for inside of Xtool F1 Ultra Laser Engraver
listings.description: With the safety shield on the Xtool F1 Ultra, it is not ideal to use a camera from outside. So, I made a 3D printed mount for an inexpensive Wyze web cam. This allows you to see the status of your engraving from anywhere while keeping your eyes safe. This comes with everything you will need except for the Wyze camera. This works with the v3 & v4 versions of the Wyze Cam.

listings.title: LizzQ Pellet Smoker Tube Filling Funnel
listings.description:
This is a 3D printed funnel system for the LizzQ pellet smoker tube. It has a base with a magnet that will hold it steady while you fill the top piece (funnel) with your choice of pellets. When not in use the two pieces lock together for convenient storage.

To see it in action you can check out my video on YouTube, https://youtu.be/Efu1WasbIc4.
